# pnpm Scripts

Use `pnpm`, never `npm` or `yarn`. Use `pnpm dlx` instead of `npx`.

## Verify Changes

```bash
pnpm check:fix   # typecheck + lint:fix + format (recommended)
pnpm check       # typecheck + lint + format:check (read-only)
```

## Individual Checks

```bash
pnpm typecheck      # Both app + node configs
pnpm typecheck:app  # tsconfig.app.json only
pnpm typecheck:node # tsconfig.node.json only
pnpm lint           # Biome + ESLint (read-only)
pnpm lint:fix       # Biome + ESLint with auto-fix
pnpm format         # Biome format (writes)
pnpm format:check   # Biome format (read-only)
```

## Build

```bash
pnpm build           # Clean + build library (JS + CSS)
pnpm build:ui:lib    # Build JS only
pnpm build:ui:css    # Build CSS only
pnpm build:storybook # Build Storybook static
pnpm build:all       # Build library + Storybook
pnpm clean           # Remove dist/, coverage/, storybook-static/
```

## Development

```bash
pnpm dev     # Storybook on port 6006
pnpm preview # Serve current dir on port 4000
```

## Analysis

```bash
pnpm size    # Check bundle size limits
pnpm analyze # Build + open bundle visualizer (dist/stats.html)
```

## Release

```bash
pnpm release:dry # Validate publish (dry run)
```

Pre-publish runs: `check → build → size`

## Testing

```bash
pnpm test    # No-op (exit 0)
pnpm test:ci # No-op (exit 0)
```

Tests not implemented yet.

## Linting Pipeline

Two tools in sequence:

1. **Biome** - TS/TSX lint + format + import sorting + Tailwind class sorting; JSON lint + format; CSS format
2. **ESLint** - React rules, jsx-a11y accessibility, TypeScript-specific rules

## Pre-commit Hook

`lint-staged` runs on commit:
- `*.{ts,tsx}` → Biome check + ESLint fix
- `*.{json,css}` → Biome check

## CI Pipeline

GitHub Actions on push/PR to master:
1. typecheck
2. lint
3. format:check
4. build
5. size

